George Kellgren, an Engineer from Sweden, moved to the US in 1979, and eventually founded the firearms company Grendel, Inc. in 1987. postcontent:
My wife and I bought this hot tub when we remodeled part of our house in 2010. We used it for the first three years minimally, and then we drained and winterized it for the last two years. Its a. Catalina Spa, rated the best at the time. It holds 6 people, and has a lot of features. 

I just filled it up today with fresh water, to make sure that it is working properly. The lights, heater, pumps waterfall, all work just like a dream. A few plastic levers need replacing. The spa has a radio/cd player with 2 speakers. The radio worked for a few minutes then? Most likely has loose wiring harness im guessing. I
Radio has power but no sound. Lastly, it needs a cover. The cover wore out, so we had it shrink wrapped for storage. They can also be purchased online for around $300. Comes with steps to get inside, all the chemicals you need. You just need a couple filters. 

We have NEVER had a problem with the spa. It has performed flawlessly. We are selling it because we never use it, and thats a shame. Someone with arthritis, fibromyalgia, or just for entertaining, its a lot of fun with minimal maintenance. 
It just needs a little tlc to be perfect. You can use it just like it is for sure, just need to purchase a cover for the winter. Im fixing to drain and clean it today. 10/5/15 1130 am.
